    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Matrix Orthogonalization Improves Memory in Recurrent Models",
      "url": "https://ayushtambde.com/blog/matrix-orthogonalization-improves-memory-in-recurrent-models/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/k9qw5n",
      "score": 1,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "Yogthos",
      "published": "2026-07-01T13:04:01Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Orthogonal transition matrices keep eigenvalues near unit norm, preventing gradient decay and significantly extending the memory horizon of recurrent neural networks.",
        "This technique enables recurrent models to capture long-range dependencies efficiently, offering an alternative to computationally expensive self-attention in Transformers.",
        "Orthogonalization principles directly optimize modern sequence models like State Space Models (SSMs), enhancing stability during long-sequence training."
      ]
    },
